---
const pageTitle = "Mandala";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(0deg);
        font-size: 260px;
        opacity: 0.12;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      p { margin: 0 0 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px 16px;
        background: var(--soft);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 4px 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        html, body { font-size: 17px; }
        h1 { font-size: 32px; }
        .frame { padding: 18px 16px 24px; }
        .symbol-bg { font-size: 180px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">symbols index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/symbols/tree-of-life">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/symbols/labyrinth">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg">◯</div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Mandala</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">symbols / center / wholeness / archive entry 005</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            The mandala is a symbolic image of wholeness. It often appears as a circle,
            a square, or a structured pattern organized around a center. Unlike symbols
            that move outward, the mandala gathers inward.
          </p>

          <p>
            Across cultures, mandalas are used in ritual, art, and meditation. They
            are not only decorative forms. They represent order emerging from chaos,
            and the presence of a center within complexity.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            the mandala does not explain the self, it reflects it.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">the hidden center</h2>

          <p>
            Psychologically, the mandala often appears when the psyche is attempting
            to restore balance. It can arise in dreams, drawings, or spontaneous
            imagination as a sign that something is organizing itself.
          </p>

          <p>
            The center of the mandala represents a point of stability that is not
            dependent on external conditions. It is not fixed identity, but a deeper
            form of coherence.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">order and integration</h2>

          <p>
            The structure of a mandala shows that opposites can exist within the same
            whole. Light and dark, movement and stillness, inner and outer. Instead of
            eliminating tension, the mandala holds it in a meaningful pattern.
          </p>

          <p>
            Because of this, the mandala is often linked to integration. It appears
            when different parts of the psyche begin to come into relation rather
            than conflict.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">back to symbols index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/labyrinth">continue to: labyrinth</a>
            <a class="red" href="/symbols/tree-of-life">tree of life</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
